The "Valid Anagram" is a common and beginner-friendly DSA interview question that checks your understanding of strings and hash maps.

âœ… Problem Statement: Valid Anagram
Given two strings s and t, return true if t is an anagram of s, and false otherwise.

ðŸ”¹ An anagram is formed by rearranging the letters of another word using all the original letters exactly once.

